{
  "texts": [
    "Subsequently, the problem of bias needs to be studied in continual (a.k.a.",
    "lifelong) learning scenarios (Lange et al., 2022), where AI models are continuously adapted to changing data.",
    "Another problem is the occurrence of feedback loops (Pagan et al., 2023; EU Agency for Fundamental Rights, 2022) (see also the notion of performative predictions (Perdomo et al., 2020)) which occur when the outputs of AI models subsequently affect the inputs to downstream systems.",
    "These vicious cycles can perpetuate unfairness even if static fair-AI models are used (Liu et al., 2018).",
    "We distinguish two main categories of model monitoring."
  ]
}